  "title": "Field Marketing Staff – Print Hub",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p><strong>Position:</strong> Field Marketing Staff – Print Hub<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Singapore</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong><br />The Field Marketing Staff is responsible for promoting Print Hub services, acquiring new clients, maintaining existing customer relationships, and achieving assigned sales targets. The role involves direct client interaction, understanding printing requirements, coordinating with internal teams, and ensuring high customer satisfaction.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Promote and market Print Hub printing services, including digital, offset, large-format, and customised printing solutions.</p></li><li><p>Conduct field visits to corporate clients, training centres, institutions, and SMEs across Singapore.</p></li><li><p>Understand customer requirements and recommend suitable printing solutions based on quality, cost, and timelines.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and follow up on quotations, proposals, and approvals.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with design, production, and operations teams to ensure accurate order execution.</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely follow-up on orders, deliveries, and post-service feedback.</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong long-term client relationships.</p></li><li><p>Handle customer queries, concerns, and basic issue resolution professionally.</p></li><li><p>Achieve assigned sales and booking targets on a weekly and monthly basis.</p></li><li><p>Maintain proper records of client interactions, orders, and follow-ups.</p></li><li><p>Adhere to company policies, branding guidelines, and professional conduct standards.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Required Skills & Competencies</strong></p><ul><li><p>Basic knowledge of printing services and materials.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills.</p></li><li><p>Customer-focused mindset with problem-solving ability.</p></li><li><p>Good time management and organisational skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</p></li><li><p>Sound decision-making skills based on customer and business needs.</p></li><li><p>Adaptability to meet changing customer demands and deadlines.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or equivalent qualification (preferred).</p></li><li><p>1–3 years of experience in marketing, sales, or the printing industry is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with the Singapore corporate and business environment is preferred.</p></li><li><p>Proficiency in English; knowledge of Tamil/Mandarin is an added advantage.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Personal Attributes</strong></p><ul><li><p>Target-driven and result-oriented.</p></li><li><p>Professional appearance and attitude.</p></li><li><p>Honest, reliable, and accountable.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to travel locally for client meetings.</p></li></ul>",
